 distinct mechanisms\nsignificantly impact the corresponding solar cell performance, and we find AX\npassivation that has not been converted to a layered perovskite allows for a\nmuch larger processing window (e.g., larger allowed variance of AX\nconcentration which is critical for improving the eventual manufacturing yield)\nand more reproducible condition to realize device performance improvements,\nwhile A2PbI4 as a passivator yields a much narrower processing window. We\nexpect these results to enable a more rational route for developing AX for\nperovskite.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Mar 2022 13:15:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
